{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_parsifal_ver01/data/sn83045462/0028060866A/1957121101/1123.xml":{"full_text":"Arends Raps\nDemocrats on\n'Missile Delay'\nBy ROBERT K. WALSH\nStung by Democratic aaser\ntion* that the Eisenhower ad\nministration was too late and\nlukewarm In the missile fle.d.\na House Republican leader\ncharged today that the Tru\nman administration did too lit\ntle\nRepresentative Arends of\nIllinois. House minority whip!\nand ranking Republican on the:\nArmed Services Committee, ac\ncused Democratic congressional\nleaders of putting \u201cour whole\nnational defense program di\nrectly into the field of politics.\u201d\nHe complained that Demo\ncratic leaders who attended\nthe White House briefing last\nweek did \"all their talking\nafter the meeting and obvious\nly for political purposes\u201d and\nto mislead the people.\nCites 1933 Start\n\u201cThe truth Is,\u201d he declared,\n\u201cthat In America for most of'\nthe twelve years since World\nWar II those in authority be\nlieved that long-range ballistic\nmissiles were not worthy of\nmajor effort. The result is we\nhave had long-range ballistic\nmissile programs of conse\nquence only since 1934. These\nprograms were impelled by\nstudies started in June. 1963.\nonly six months after Presi\ndent Eisenhower took office.\n\u201cThis means that for eight\ncritical postwar years, while\nthe Soviet Union evidently was\ngoing ahead full blast with\ntheir long-range rocketry, the\nUnited States was giving at\ntention to other things. Today\nwe spend in just a few hours\nas much on those programs as\nwe spent In an entire year just\nfive years ago. Os the several\nlong-range ballistic missiles now\nunder way. only one\u2014the Atlas\n\u2014even existed before President\nEisenhower took office.\u201d\nThe charges by Mr Arends\nwere the hardest-hitting and\nmost sweeping by any Repub\nlican congressional leader thus\nfar. They indicated a more\ncomprehensive and compact\neffort to counteract complaints'\nby several Democratic leaders\nthat the Eisenhower adminis\ntration failed to show a suffi-i\neient sense of urgency and effl- i\nciency in developing missile\nand satellite programs\nNation\u2019s Prime Need\nMr. Arends emphasized that\nthe prime need now is to keep\nthe United States from falling\nbehind in the scientific and\ntechnological race between\nnow and 1957.\"\nHe contended the Republi\ncan! \"have diligently avoided\nany political partisanship in\nconnection with all national\ndefense matters.\" He said he\ndeplored Democratic \u201cpolitical\nclaptrap. He complained that\nDemocratic National Chairman\nPaul Butler \"has gone so far;\nas to try to bring our dis\ntinguished and conscientious\nscientists into public disre\npute.\"\n\u201cWhile failures are to be ex\npected in any scientific experi\nment, the results under the\nadministration's program are\nsure to be gratifying We have\nsurged forward so fast in so\nshort a time to justify full con\nfidence in our efforts.\" he said.\nEisenhower\nResignation\nCall Rapped\nSenator Neuberger. Democrat\nof Oregon. Is opposed to recent\nsuggestions that President Eis\nenhower resign because of his\nhealth.\nIn announcing his position,\nhe took direct issue with his\nDemocratic colleague. Senator\nMorse of Oregon, who was one!\nof the first to suggest that Mr.\nEisenhower turn the reins of\nGovernment over to Vice Presi\ndent Nixon.\n\u201cSuch an abdication should\nnever take place unless the most\nrespected medical authorities\nin the Nation would certify that\nthe President had absolutely no\nhope of recovery from a disease\nwhich totally incapacitated him\nfor service.\u201d Senator Neuberger\nsaid.\nThe Senator said an un\ntenable situation would exist\nif the President resigned and\nlater made a full recovery\n\"To whom would the public\nlook for leadership to the\nVice President occupying the\nWhite House, or to the real\nPresident, playing golf or\nshooting grouse at some re\ntreat?\" he asked.\nThe Oregon Senator recalled\nthat President Cleveland un\nderwent surgery for cancer of\nthe jaw in 1893 but continued\nto serve for more than three\nyears and retired in fairly sound\nhealth. Senator Neuberger said\nthat if the present mood had\nexisted then Mr Cleveland\nwould have abdicated after the\noperation.\nf\nCitizens Unit Approves\nIllegitimacy Study\nMembers of the Port Du\npont Citizens Association arej\npleased with the six-month i\nstudy of Washington teen- i\nage illegitimacy the District\nCommissioners approved yes\nterday.\nThey resolved to write a let-\nter to the Commissioners, ex\npressing their approval of the\nstudy, to be undertaken by the\nCommissioners Youth Council.\nThe meeting was held in the\nAnne Beers School at Thirty\nsixth street and Alabama ave\nnue S.E. and was conducted\nby .President Charles A. Fro\nmaf> I\nAll 4 HUB Stores OpenEveryNightUnti^*O^^M.\n9L JW j B V B B W V V B M Ms B jB B W B M Wb BBF\nj JB |B MB w M 1 B w B Jm I df B BH| B| X JPP M Jk W&\n1 Hollywood Bed with Brass Headboard\ns l4 ss j^gso\n\u2022f sligkr unnoticeoble irregular- m mm m m m N,w telly georonteed. Hoi\nitie*! Alio, oibor nsot of cow r \"Ope .akMsE?\"\u2014 -C. Effff \u00abO.ffl/n fmm \\mmmmm iorge site porcelom tub and sotefy\nj \u201eHH.\n25% Wotl Blanktt Plastic Hassocks\nly CANNON MILLS! I Washington at all HlB stores\u2019 4\nsett. worm, ond durable Choose r# n <i ort\n.\u2014j\nOur Reg. Price $249.95 Our Reg. Price $249.95 Q ur p eg p rxre g 69 9\n8-Pe. Walsat Vaster Bedroom Grasp Modars 8-Pe. Living Room Omtfit 5-Pe. Chrome or Wrosght Iran Dinette\nDOUbl l S\u00abfl AO ComfcrtoW. Jr*. o\u00abd lorgo molchrng Arm Chen Cgfl flfl Smcr. modern Extension toble with loaf bo, merproof C M Oft\nChest and Bookcase Bed. plus on Innersprmg Mot- m LI W in your choice of smort modem fobrics. Also, a T II JMMM V Q\nM trosv. Box Spring ond 2 Pillows. Quolity mode with I wrought iron TV Choir covered in plostK, 3 blond IJJ plo,t,c ,op in y ur cho,c of colors. 4 Choirs with